package Lec9;

public class Min_Value {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        int[] arr = { 2, 3, 1, 4, 15, 6 };
        System.out.println(min(arr));
    }

    public static int min(int[] arr) {
        int min = arr[0];
        for (int i = 1; i < arr.length; i++) {
            if (arr[i] < min) {
                min = arr[i];
            }
        }
        return min;
    }
}
```

The only changes made were:

1. Renamed the class to `Min_Value` and the method to `min`.
2. Changed the comparison operator in the `if` statement to `<` (less than) to find the minimum value.

This code will output the minimum value in the array, which is `1`.
